<div class="webex-question">
<div class="webex-check webex-box">
<p>What is the distance between the two points <span class="math inline">\(p = (2, 4)\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(q = (5, 5)\)</span> in a Cartesian coordinate system?</p>
<div id="radio_group_doplinltir" class="webex-radiogroup">
<label><input type='radio' autocomplete='off' name='radio_group_doplinltir' value=''/><span><span class="math inline">\(1.261\)</span></span></label><label><input type='radio' autocomplete='off' name='radio_group_doplinltir' value=''/><span><span class="math inline">\(2.000\)</span></span></label><label><input type='radio' autocomplete='off' name='radio_group_doplinltir' value=''/><span><span class="math inline">\(2.695\)</span></span></label><label><input type='radio' autocomplete='off' name='radio_group_doplinltir' value=''/><span><span class="math inline">\(0.408\)</span></span></label><label><input type='radio' autocomplete='off' name='radio_group_doplinltir' value='answer'/><span><span class="math inline">\(3.162\)</span></span></label>
</div>
</div>
<div class="webex-solution">
<p>The distance <span class="math inline">\(d\)</span> of <span class="math inline">\(p\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(q\)</span> is given by <span class="math inline">\(d^2 = (p_1 - q_1)^2 + (p_2 - q_2)^2\)</span> (Pythagorean formula).</p>
<p>Hence <span class="math inline">\(d = \sqrt{(p_1 - q_1)^2 + (p_2 - q_2)^2} =  \sqrt{(2 - 5)^2 + (4 - 5)^2}  = 3.162\)</span>.<br />
<img src="data:image/png;base64," /></p>
<ul>
<li>False</li>
<li>False</li>
<li>False</li>
<li>False</li>
<li>True</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="webex-solution">
<p>The distance <span class="math inline">\(d\)</span> of <span class="math inline">\(p\)</span> and <span class="math inline">\(q\)</span> is given by <span class="math inline">\(d^2 = (p_1 - q_1)^2 + (p_2 - q_2)^2\)</span> (Pythagorean formula).</p>
<p>Hence <span class="math inline">\(d = \sqrt{(p_1 - q_1)^2 + (p_2 - q_2)^2} =  \sqrt{(1 - 4)^2 + (5 - 2)^2}  = 4.243\)</span>.<br />

<div class='row t20 b1'>
  <div class='medium-4 columns'><b>Description:</b></div>
  <div class='medium-8 columns'>Computing the (Euclidean) distance between two randomly-drawn points by using the Pythagorean Theorem. In addition to the correct solution, four false alternatives are generated through <code class="highlighter-rouge">num_to_schoice()</code> by providing two common errors along with a range and minimal delta for two further random solutions.</div>
</div>
